\par Misconceptions about simple notions 
in arithmetic are not readily given up. So for example, a child who believes that 1/4 is larger than 1/2 will not let go of this misconception when he or she gets back an assignment full of red correction marks. The child will let go of this misconception
 when he or she fully understands fractions. So, how do we develop this understanding?}{\insrsid8602064 
